channel.title: CVE Feed for Jenkins project -- Jenkins Autocomplete Parameter Plugin
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Jenkins project -- Jenkins Autocomplete Parameter Plugin

item.title: CVE-2022-30969|2024-08-03T07:03:39.913Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20autocomplete%20parameter%20plugin
item.description: A cross-site request forgery (CSRF) vulnerability in Jenkins Autocomplete Parameter Plugin 1.1 and earlier allows attackers to execute arbitrary code without sandbox protection if the victim is an administrator.

item.title: CVE-2022-30970|2024-08-03T07:03:40.038Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20autocomplete%20parameter%20plugin
item.description: Jenkins Autocomplete Parameter Plugin 1.1 and earlier references Dropdown Autocomplete parameter and Auto Complete String parameter names in an unsafe manner from Javascript embedded in view definitions, resulting in a stored cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability exploitable by attackers with Item/Configure permission.

item.title: CVE-2022-30961|2024-08-03T07:03:39.861Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20autocomplete%20parameter%20plugin
item.description: Jenkins Autocomplete Parameter Plugin 1.1 and earlier does not escape the name of Dropdown Autocomplete and Auto Complete String parameters on views displaying parameters, resulting in a stored cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability exploitable by attackers with Item/Configure permission.
